<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Use an incline bench set at a 45-degree angle, allowing your arms to hang freely. Keep your chest against the bench for stability and to isolate the short head of your biceps.</li>



<li>Focus on controlled and deliberate curls, ensuring a full range of motion. Squeeze your biceps at the top of each rep to maximize muscle engagement.</li>



<li>Keep your elbows in front of your body throughout the exercise to emphasize the short head of the biceps. Avoid swinging or using momentum to lift the weight, maintaining strict form for optimal results.</li>
